  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul at a different location is a common practice and generally straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n**1. Confirm \"One-Way\" Rental:**\n\n*   **Crucially, you must have reserved a one-way rental.** This is the foundation of dropping off at a different location. If you booked a \"round trip\" or \"in-town\" rental, you *must* return the U-Haul to the original pickup location. Changing to a one-way rental may incur additional fees and may not be possible depending on U-Haul's availability and needs.\n\n**2. Confirm Your Drop-Off Location (and Drop-Off Date/Time):**\n\n*   **Review your rental agreement:** This document should clearly state the agreed-upon drop-off location. **Double-check this information!**\n*   **Call U-Haul (preferred):** Contact U-Haul customer service (1-800-GO-U-HAUL) or the drop-off location directly a day or two before your expected arrival. Reconfirm the address, operating hours, and any specific instructions they might have. Sometimes locations have specific areas for after-hours drop-offs or unique procedures.\n*   **U-Haul Website/App:** Some U-Haul accounts allow you to verify your reservation details, including the drop-off location, online or through the mobile app.\n\n**3. What to Do Upon Arrival at the Drop-Off Location:**\n\n*   **During Business Hours:**\n    *   Park the U-Haul in a designated area, if indicated.\n    *   Go inside the U-Haul location and speak with a representative.  They will inspect the vehicle, record the mileage, fuel level, and any damage, and provide you with a final receipt.\n    *   Return the keys to the representative.\n    *   Confirm that you receive a signed or stamped copy of the final rental agreement.  This is your proof of return.\n\n*   **After Business Hours (Key Drop):**\n    *   **Only do this if the location is closed and you have confirmed this is acceptable.**  Otherwise, you'll be charged for extra days until they open.\n    *   Park the U-Haul in a designated area, if indicated. Try to park it securely and out of the way.  If there is no designated area, park it in a place that is easily accessible and does not block other vehicles or traffic.\n    *   Fill out the after-hours drop-off envelope (usually located near the key drop box). You'll need to record:\n        *   Truck/Trailer Number\n        *   Mileage\n        *   Fuel Level (Be as accurate as possible; U-Haul will likely charge if it's below the level specified in your agreement.)\n        *   Date and Time of Drop-Off\n        *   Your Name and Contact Information\n    *   Place the keys and the completed envelope in the designated key drop box.\n    *   **Take pictures!**  Photograph the truck/trailer's exterior, the mileage reading, the fuel level, and the parking location. This documentation is important in case of any discrepancies.\n\n**4. After Drop-Off:**\n\n*   **Check Your Email:** U-Haul usually sends a final confirmation email with your charges.  Review this email carefully to ensure accuracy.\n*   **Keep Your Documentation:** Retain your rental agreement and any pictures or notes you took until you are certain you have been billed correctly.\n*   **Dispute Any Discrepancies Immediately:** If you notice any errors in your bill (e.g., incorrect mileage, fuel charges, or damage claims you don't believe are valid), contact U-Haul customer service *immediately* to dispute the charges. Have your documentation ready to support your claim.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Fuel:** Return the U-Haul with the same fuel level as when you picked it up (usually specified on your rental agreement). U-Haul will charge you a higher rate per gallon if you don't.\n*   **Cleanliness:** While you don't have to deep-clean the U-Haul, it's courteous to remove any trash and debris.  You may be charged a cleaning fee if the truck is left excessively dirty.\n*   **Mileage:** Be aware of the mileage limit specified in your rental agreement. You'll be charged a per-mile fee for exceeding it.\n*   **Damage:** Inspect the U-Haul thoroughly *before* you pick it up and note any existing damage on your rental agreement.  This will protect you from being charged for damage you didn't cause. Do the same upon returning it and take pictures.\n*   **Late Returns:** Returning the U-Haul late will result in additional charges. If you anticipate being late, contact U-Haul as soon as possible to discuss your options. They may be able to adjust your reservation (though this isn't guaranteed).\n*   **Location Types:** U-Haul has different types of locations (company-owned, independent dealers, etc.). The procedures may vary slightly, so confirming with your specific drop-off location is always recommended.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure a smooth and hassle-free U-Haul drop-off experience. Remember, communication is key. Contact U-Haul if you have any questions or concerns.\n",
